  "detailed_description": "<strong>Thrusta X is a 2D retro-style shoot'em-up where the goal is to convey an experience rather than acquiring a high score or the best upgrades.<br>It isn't only about flying from left to right and blasting enemies. Stages throw a variety of surprises at you.<br>Story, puzzle, and battle elements are combined into one flowing adventure.</strong><br><br><i>The late Professor designed & built a craft to free the world of tyranny.<br>It is left to you & your faithful robot guide to undo the Darklord’s corruption of the world one mission at a time.<br>The souls of the Golden Lords must be freed.</i><br><br>Varied environments & evolving storyline.<br>Shoot to kill, shoot to solve puzzles.<br><br>2D, pixel-art-based graphics and full hi-def soundtrack.<br>60 FPS for fast and responsive gameplay.<br>Two difficulty levels.<br>Simple controls but varied play modes keep things interesting.<br>Eleven lands & 55 levels. <br>Xbox (or Xbox compatible) controller recommended.",
  "about_the_game": "<strong>Thrusta X is a 2D retro-style shoot'em-up where the goal is to convey an experience rather than acquiring a high score or the best upgrades.<br>It isn't only about flying from left to right and blasting enemies. Stages throw a variety of surprises at you.<br>Story, puzzle, and battle elements are combined into one flowing adventure.</strong><br><br><i>The late Professor designed & built a craft to free the world of tyranny.<br>It is left to you & your faithful robot guide to undo the Darklord’s corruption of the world one mission at a time.<br>The souls of the Golden Lords must be freed.</i><br><br>Varied environments & evolving storyline.<br>Shoot to kill, shoot to solve puzzles.<br><br>2D, pixel-art-based graphics and full hi-def soundtrack.<br>60 FPS for fast and responsive gameplay.<br>Two difficulty levels.<br>Simple controls but varied play modes keep things interesting.<br>Eleven lands & 55 levels. <br>Xbox (or Xbox compatible) controller recommended.",
